Scala supports lazy evaluation while Java does not

Readability is less in Scala whereas it is more in Java

Scala is a combination of both object oriented and functional programming while Java is a general purpose object oriented language

Scala supports operator overloading while Java does not

Scala code is written in compact form while Java code is written in long form

Scala variables are by default immutable while Java variables are by default mutable

Scala treats every function as a variable while Java treats treats them as objects